ate in them. People on the boards on discussions will call you on shit. And you'd best be prepared to defend/explain your position. It's in some cases like a debate. So sometimes I don't have the time or energy to devote to participating in that in certain threads. Sometimes they become so interesting that I'll jump in on later pages because I can no longer help myself.<br><br>You made a statement on another thread. Perhaps that wasn't how you intended it to be taken. Doesn't matter. You made a statement. People disagreed with you, and the thread went off track. <br><br>Now, I have personally picked the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> shit</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> out of some people's posts on occasion. To the point where some people post &quot;Gee, don't ever piss Tarot off&quot;. Which when stated I tend to find kinda funny and kinda scary. When I pick the shit out of someone's posts, I'm generally doing so for a very specific purpose. I'm dismantling what they're saying. If they want to respond, they can pick apart mine, but they're gonna have to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> think</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to do it.<br><br>And hopefully in the end, we'll not only be entertained, but maybe even learn something.<br><br>Some people are brutal in how they do that though. And some people, let's be honest, are real assholes on this board. So? The people who are pricks, I certainly don't value their opinion. And in not valuing their opinion, I don't really care what they have to say. To me it has no merit. Sure, if they attacked me I may or may not call them on it, but since I don't give a damn what they think, it's not like it bothers me personally.<br><br>Beyond the bullshit, and crap, and humor...did you LEARN anything from that thread? Did you see anything you hadn't seen before? Did it cause you to evaluate how you state things, or perhaps even how you might think about things? Did you see another person's perspective you weren't aware of?<br><br>Uncomfortable? Sure. Sometimes it is.<br><br>But if you GAINED anything from it, then what immense value it has.<br><br>Believe me, there have been times when I've seen some things on this board I've been an inch away from leaving this board for good. Basically because of a couple of people. I've gone so far at one point to tell Leolan I'm done with it, and attempted to quit. The bastard wouldn't let me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>And in the position I'm in, I could have easily banned that person over the situation I found so personally abhorant. I have the power to do so, and frankly could have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> easily</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> done it...even probably with a lot of support from the community.<br><br>I didn't though. Mainly because as shitty as I found it, and as easily as it would have been to ban them, I don't like to ban people. Everyone makes up this community, not just the people I don't like. However we've tried to develop more rules to make the majority more comfortable while infringing on the least amount of people. Hopefully that works as well as anything can.<br><br>My entire point here is, that there are things about this community I don't like, and threads I've seen that make me frankly want to puke. However for the most part I do like it. If I gain a perspective on an issue, or am forced to think or rethink anything...I've gained a great deal.<br><br>That's what I get from the community, besides being amused. Besides news and gossip. Besides EQ by proxy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I sometimes gain enlightenment. And that's why I'm still around.<br><br>I'd urge to you take a step back, take a deep breath and ask yourself why do you want to leave. And what you get out of posting. If you're pissy because your pride is hurt, or your feelings got hurt, take a look at why. <br><br>I think you do get something from Lanys. I really do. I also think you contribute to Lanys as well.<br><br> And I think that perhaps why you're leaving is wrong for you. I hope you rethink it in any case. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.anarchyboard.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://users.gloryroad.net/~arathorn/Tarotsign.jpg" border="0"></a> <br><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Realm </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Everquest: Fennin Ro, Karana, Ero Marr & Lanys T'Vyl </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Ultima Online: Catskills </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>INACTIVE</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Anarchy Online: Beta Tester, Rubi-Ka 1 </FONT><FONT COLOR=FF0000 SIZE=1>RETIRED</FONT><BR><FONT COLOR=000000 SIZE=1>Dark Age of Camelot: Beta Tester;Merlin Midgard</FONT><FONT COLOR=008000 SIZE=1> CURRENT</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usnarky00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snarky00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/7/02 12:12:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1668.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.glitchless.com/root/sunset.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Final Rant.</span><hr size=1> Tarot you make the assumption that because some people dont write down their whole thought process and explain it in detail they didnt have one =P<br><br>Beleive me most of my posts are the 'short and sweet' kind but that doesnt mea